<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="578" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,151,1949]" box="[199,895,511,536]" pageId="5" pageNumber="578">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,412,511,536]" pageId="5" pageNumber="578">Description. Male</emphasis>
(n = 24). Total length 2.2–4.2, 2.9 (8) mm.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,151,1949]" pageId="5" pageNumber="578">
<emphasis box="[199,329,548,573]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="578">Coloration.</emphasis>
Generally green. Wing without any marking. Foreleg pale yellow with base and sub-apex of femora, apices of tibia and tarsomere 1, and tarsomeres 2–5 dark brown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,151,1949]" pageId="5" pageNumber="578">
<emphasis box="[199,260,620,645]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="578">Head</emphasis>
. Temporals 8–14, 11. Frontal tubercles absent. AR 0.24–0.31, 0.26 (22). Palpomere 3 apically with 2 sensilla clavata, longest 23–28, 26 (18) µm long. Pm4/Pm3 1.3–1.6, 1.5 (21); Pm5/Pm4 1.2–1.4, 1.3 (21).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,151,1949]" box="[199,1332,694,719]" pageId="5" pageNumber="578">
<emphasis box="[199,280,694,719]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="578">Thorax</emphasis>
. Acrostichals 14–23, 17; dorsocentrals 8–16, 12 (23); prealars 3–5, 4. Scutellum with 2 setae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,151,1949]" pageId="5" pageNumber="578">
<emphasis box="[199,264,732,755]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="578">Wing.</emphasis>
Length 1.3–2.2, 1.9 (23) mm. VR 1.3–1.5, 1.4 (23). Brachiolum with 1 (8) seta; R with 9–20, 14 (8) setae; R1 with 7–16, 12 (8) setae; R4+5 with 2–19, 10 (8) setae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,151,1949]" pageId="5" pageNumber="578">
<emphasis box="[199,259,806,829]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="578">Legs.</emphasis>
Mid tarsomere 1 with 1–5, 3 (20) sensilla chaetica, distalmost located 0.14–0.31, 0.21 (20) from apex. LR1 1.37–1.54, 1.46 (16); LR2 0.54–0.62, 0.58 (23); LR3 0.52–0.58, 0.56 (23).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,151,1949]" pageId="5" pageNumber="578">
<emphasis box="[199,342,881,904]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="578">Hypopygium</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[357,522,880,905]" captionStart="FIGURES 10 – 13" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1286,1309]" captionTargetBox="[276,1303,210,1241]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[266,1321,195,1265]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 10 – 13. Nilothauma hibaratertium Sasa, male. 10, hypopygium, ventral view (right) and dorsal view (left); 11, anal tergite with anal point, lateral view; 12 a – c, anterior projection on anal tergite, dorsal view, showing variation; 13, superior volsella, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1051816/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="578">Figures 10, 11</figureCitation>
). Tergite IX with 2 dorsal projections and 9–17, 13 (10) posterior setae. Anterior projection (
<figureCitation box="[283,448,916,941]" captionStart="FIGURES 10 – 13" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1286,1309]" captionTargetBox="[276,1303,210,1241]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[266,1321,195,1265]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 10 – 13. Nilothauma hibaratertium Sasa, male. 10, hypopygium, ventral view (right) and dorsal view (left); 11, anal tergite with anal point, lateral view; 12 a – c, anterior projection on anal tergite, dorsal view, showing variation; 13, superior volsella, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1051816/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="578">Figures 12a–c</figureCitation>
) 18–38, 28 (22) µm long, 0.75–1.2, 0.95 (22) times as long as broad, varying from simple lobe to two distinctly divided lobes, usually notched posteriorly, with about 20–50 plumose setae 40–59, 50 (22) µm long. Posterior projection 22–38, 30 (13) µm long, 0.73–1.2, 0.89 (11) times as long as basal width, basally microtrichiose, apically with 6–15, 9 (15) setae 12–20, 16 (17) µm long. Anal point 55–63, 59 (6) µm long, 1.8–1.9, 1.9 (6) times as long as broad, without microtrichia. Laterosternite IX with 2–7, 4 setae. Phallapodeme 50– 75, 64 (20) µm long. Sternapodeme bluntly triangular. Gonocoxite 88–125, 114 (22) µm long. Superior volsella (
<figureCitation box="[158,272,1132,1157]" captionStart="FIGURES 10 – 13" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1286,1309]" captionTargetBox="[276,1303,210,1241]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[266,1321,195,1265]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 10 – 13. Nilothauma hibaratertium Sasa, male. 10, hypopygium, ventral view (right) and dorsal view (left); 11, anal tergite with anal point, lateral view; 12 a – c, anterior projection on anal tergite, dorsal view, showing variation; 13, superior volsella, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1051816/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="578">Figure 13</figureCitation>
) pad-like, 37–50, 44 (22) µm long, microtrichiose with 1 long lateral and 5–8, 6 (21) short marginal setae on small tubercles; lateral seta 25–42, 32 (19) µm long. Median volsella 5–8, 7 (23) µm long, with 2–4, 3 (23) apical setae on small tubercles. Inferior volsella microtrichiose, with 7–10, 8 apically split setae. Gonostylus 105– 168, 149 (22) µm long, 5.3–5.9, 5.6 (6) times as long as broad at middle, parallel-sided for most of its length, with pointed apex; distal-median setae 6–10, 8 (22), uniserial, some split apically. HR 0.71–0.83, 0.77 (22).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="578" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,151,1949]" pageId="5" pageNumber="578">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1312,1337]" pageId="5" pageNumber="578">Remarks.</emphasis>
The male of 
<taxonomicName authority="Adam &amp; Saether, 1999" authorityName="Adam &amp; Saether. Recently I" authorityYear="1999" box="[468,929,1312,1337]" class="Insecta" family="Chironomidae" genus="Nilothauma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="578" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sasai">
<emphasis box="[468,666,1312,1337]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="578">Nilothauma sasai</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Adam" box="[675,929,1312,1337]" pageId="5" pageNumber="578" refString="Adam, J. I. &amp; Saether, O. A. (1999) Revision of the genus Nilothauma Kieffer, 1921 (Diptera: Chironomidae). Entomologica scandinavica, 56 (Supplement), 1 - 107." type="journal article" year="1999">Adam &amp; Saether, 1999</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
was separated from that of 
<taxonomicName authority="Sasa, 1993" authorityName="Sasa" authorityYear="1993" class="Insecta" family="Chironomidae" genus="Nilothauma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="578" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hibaratertium">
<emphasis box="[1246,1436,1312,1337]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="578">N. hibaratertium</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Sasa" box="[151,276,1349,1373]" pageId="5" pageNumber="578" refString="Sasa, M. (1993) Studies on the chironomid midges (yusurika) collected in Toyama and other areas of Japan, 1993. Part 5. The chironomids collected from lakes in the Aizu district (Fukushima). Research Report from Toyama Prefectural environmental Pollution Research Centre, 1993, 69 - 95." type="journal article" year="1993">Sasa, 1993</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
by the simple anterior projection on tergite IX (see the key to male imagines, fig. 23F in 
<bibRefCitation author="Adam" pageId="5" pageNumber="578" refString="Adam, J. I. &amp; Saether, O. A. (1999) Revision of the genus Nilothauma Kieffer, 1921 (Diptera: Chironomidae). Entomologica scandinavica, 56 (Supplement), 1 - 107." type="journal article" year="1999">Adam &amp; Saether 1999</bibRefCitation>
). However, re-examination of the 
<typeStatus box="[689,787,1384,1409]" pageId="5" pageNumber="578">holotype</typeStatus>
male of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Adam &amp; Saether. Recently I" authorityYear="1999" box="[891,984,1385,1408]" class="Insecta" family="Chironomidae" genus="Nilothauma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="578" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sasai">
<emphasis box="[891,984,1385,1408]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="578">N. sasai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
disclosed that the anterior projection is completely split into two lobes in conflict with the original description. I re-examined the following 
<typeStatus box="[1285,1333,1421,1445]" pageId="5" pageNumber="578">type</typeStatus>
series of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sasa" authorityYear="1993" box="[151,344,1456,1481]" class="Insecta" family="Chironomidae" genus="Nilothauma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="578" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hibaratertium">
<emphasis box="[151,344,1456,1481]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="578">N. hibaratertium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Sasa, Suzuki &amp; Sakai, 1998" authorityName="Sasa, Suzuki &amp; Sakai" authorityYear="1998" box="[406,1031,1456,1481]" class="Insecta" family="Chironomidae" genus="Tosayusurika" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="578" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="simantofea">
<emphasis box="[406,688,1456,1481]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="578">Tosayusurika simantofea</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Sasa" box="[700,1031,1456,1481]" pageId="5" pageNumber="578" refString="Sasa, M., Suzuki, H. &amp; Sakai, T. (1998) Studies on the chironomid midges collected on the shore of Shimanto River in April, 1998. Part 1. Description of species of the subfamily Chironominae. Tropical Medicine, 40, 47 - 89." type="journal article" year="1998">Sasa, Suzuki &amp; Sakai, 1998</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, synonymized by 
<bibRefCitation author="Adam" pageId="5" pageNumber="578" refString="Adam, J. I. &amp; Saether, O. A. (1999) Revision of the genus Nilothauma Kieffer, 1921 (Diptera: Chironomidae). Entomologica scandinavica, 56 (Supplement), 1 - 107." type="journal article" year="1999">Adam &amp; Saether (1999)</bibRefCitation>
: three male specimens of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sasa" authorityYear="1993" box="[531,721,1492,1517]" class="Insecta" family="Chironomidae" genus="Nilothauma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="578" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hibaratertium">
<emphasis box="[531,721,1492,1517]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="578">N. hibaratertium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<specimenCount box="[780,872,1492,1517]" pageId="5" pageNumber="578" type="male">13 male</specimenCount>
specimens of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sasa, Suzuki &amp; Sakai" authorityYear="1998" box="[1040,1320,1492,1517]" class="Insecta" family="Chironomidae" genus="Tosayusurika" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="578" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="simantofea">
<emphasis box="[1040,1320,1492,1517]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="578">Tosayusurika simantofea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
including each 
<typeStatus box="[208,310,1528,1553]" pageId="5" pageNumber="578">holotype</typeStatus>
. Consequently, it was revealed that the anterior projection in the 
<typeStatus box="[1030,1126,1529,1553]" pageId="5" pageNumber="578">paratype</typeStatus>
No. 359: 3 of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sasa, Suzuki &amp; Sakai" authorityYear="1998" box="[1286,1436,1529,1553]" class="Insecta" family="Chironomidae" genus="Tosayusurika" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="578" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="simantofea">
<emphasis box="[1286,1436,1529,1553]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="578">T. simantofea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is simple, not divided into two lobes. These show that the simple anterior projection is an individual variation in the species and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Adam &amp; Saether. Recently I" authorityYear="1999" box="[286,377,1601,1624]" class="Insecta" family="Chironomidae" genus="Nilothauma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="578" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sasai">
<emphasis box="[286,377,1601,1624]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="578">N. sasai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sasa" authorityYear="1993" box="[642,831,1600,1625]" class="Insecta" family="Chironomidae" genus="Nilothauma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="578" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hibaratertium">
<emphasis box="[642,831,1600,1625]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="578">N. hibaratertium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,151,1949]" pageId="5" pageNumber="578">
I examined 
<specimenCount box="[331,431,1636,1661]" pageId="5" pageNumber="578" type="male">23 males</specimenCount>
of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sasa" authorityYear="1993" box="[468,656,1636,1661]" class="Insecta" family="Chironomidae" genus="Nilothauma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="578" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hibaratertium">
<emphasis box="[468,656,1636,1661]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="578">N. hibaratertium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, including seven newly collected males. They showed great variation in the morphology of the anterior anal tergal projection: in four specimens (17%) the projection is completely divided into two lobes (
<figureCitation box="[420,547,1708,1733]" captionStart="FIGURES 10 – 13" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1286,1309]" captionTargetBox="[276,1303,210,1241]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[266,1321,195,1265]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 10 – 13. Nilothauma hibaratertium Sasa, male. 10, hypopygium, ventral view (right) and dorsal view (left); 11, anal tergite with anal point, lateral view; 12 a – c, anterior projection on anal tergite, dorsal view, showing variation; 13, superior volsella, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1051816/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="578">Figure 12a</figureCitation>
), in 
<specimenCount box="[599,752,1708,1733]" pageId="5" pageNumber="578" type="generic">16 specimens</specimenCount>
(70%) the projection is notched to a varying degree (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 10 – 13" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1286,1309]" captionTargetBox="[276,1303,210,1241]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[266,1321,195,1265]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 10 – 13. Nilothauma hibaratertium Sasa, male. 10, hypopygium, ventral view (right) and dorsal view (left); 11, anal tergite with anal point, lateral view; 12 a – c, anterior projection on anal tergite, dorsal view, showing variation; 13, superior volsella, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1051816/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="578">Figure 12b</figureCitation>
), and in three specimens (13%) the projection is simple (
<figureCitation box="[836,963,1744,1769]" captionStart="FIGURES 10 – 13" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1286,1309]" captionTargetBox="[276,1303,210,1241]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[266,1321,195,1265]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 10 – 13. Nilothauma hibaratertium Sasa, male. 10, hypopygium, ventral view (right) and dorsal view (left); 11, anal tergite with anal point, lateral view; 12 a – c, anterior projection on anal tergite, dorsal view, showing variation; 13, superior volsella, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1051816/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="578">Figure 12c</figureCitation>
). The original description of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Adam &amp; Saether. Recently I" authorityYear="1999" box="[1290,1380,1745,1768]" class="Insecta" family="Chironomidae" genus="Nilothauma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="578" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sasai">
<emphasis box="[1290,1380,1745,1768]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="578">N. sasai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
may be based on another loaned specimen, not returned to me.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,151,1949]" pageId="5" pageNumber="578">
<bibRefCitation author="Adam" box="[199,541,1816,1841]" pageId="5" pageNumber="578" refString="Adam, J. I. &amp; Saether, O. A. (1999) Revision of the genus Nilothauma Kieffer, 1921 (Diptera: Chironomidae). Entomologica scandinavica, 56 (Supplement), 1 - 107." type="journal article" year="1999">Adam &amp; Saether (1999: 71)</bibRefCitation>
regarded the Portuguese species illustrated under the name of 
<taxonomicName authority="(Goetghebuer)" authorityName="Goetghebuer" baseAuthorityName="Goetghebuer" baseAuthorityYear="1921" class="Insecta" family="Chironomidae" genus="Nilothauma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="578" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brayi">
<emphasis box="[1335,1435,1816,1841]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="578">N. brayi</emphasis>
(Goetghebuer)
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Cranston" box="[355,589,1852,1877]" pageId="5" pageNumber="578" refString="Cranston, P. S., Dillon, M. E., Pinder, L. C. V. &amp; Reiss, F. (1989) 10. The adult males of Chironominae (Diptera: Chironomidae) of the Holarctic region - Keys and diagnoses. In: Wiederholm, T. (Ed.), Chironomidae of the Holarctic region. Keys and diagnoses. Part 3. Adult males. Entomologica scandinavica, 34 (Supplement), 353 - 502." type="journal article" year="1989">
Cranston 
<emphasis box="[462,511,1852,1877]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="578">et al</emphasis>
. (1989
</bibRefCitation>
fig. 10.41) as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sasa" authorityYear="1993" box="[748,936,1852,1877]" class="Insecta" family="Chironomidae" genus="Nilothauma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="578" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hibaratertium">
<emphasis box="[748,936,1852,1877]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="578">N. hibaratertium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. However, the species may be different from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sasa" authorityYear="1993" box="[151,342,1888,1913]" class="Insecta" family="Chironomidae" genus="Nilothauma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="578" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hibaratertium">
<emphasis box="[151,342,1888,1913]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="578">N. hibaratertium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
because of the stout and triangular posterior projection on the male anal tergite. The posterior projection is relatively slender and club-shaped in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sasa" authorityYear="1993" box="[716,904,1924,1949]" class="Insecta" family="Chironomidae" genus="Nilothauma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="578" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hibaratertium">
<emphasis box="[716,904,1924,1949]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="578">N. hibaratertium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
